					Title: <b>Changing Data directory location on Bitcoin-qt?</b><br />
					Post by: <b>Infinity1</b> on <b>November 23, 2012, 04:33:34 AM</b>
					<hr />
					<div style="margin: 0 5ex;">I&#039;m currently on a dual-boot setup and have my blockchain and wallet in my Windows XP partition and want to use Bitcoin on my Windows 7 partition. <br />The problem is that if I try to open Bitcoin on my Windows 7 partition I&#039;m forced to re-download the blockchain and obtain a new wallet.<br /><br />Is there anyway to change the data directory location so that Bitcoin clients will share the same location? I can&#039;t seem to find the option in Bitcoin-qt and hope they implement this in the next version.</div>
					<br />
					<hr size="2" width="100%" />
					Title: <b>Re: Changing Data directory location on Bitcoin-qt?</b><br />
					Post by: <b>niko</b> on <b>November 23, 2012, 05:31:04 AM</b>
					<hr />
					<div style="margin: 0 5ex;">Yes, add &quot;-datadir=&lt;dir&gt;&quot; to your target. <br />If you are moving databases to another directory, you&#039;ll want to tick the &quot;detach databases at shutdown&quot; option in bitcoin-qt.<br /></div>
